What is the profile of each cluster?¶

  • This results shows "Pct_Native_American","Pct_Students_With_Disabilities", "Pct_Native_Hawaiian_Pacific_Isla",Pct_Males,Pct_Females and "Pct_MultiRace_NonHispanic" are NOT an important factors since about the equal number of students (as indicated by the fact that the mean in each cluster is almost same) and also

Profiling

  • cluster 0: high english speakers and low learners with low needs and low in case of economic disadvantage with more whites and low african americans,asians and hispanics.
  • cluster 1: Low english speakers, high learners who have high needs are economically highly disadvantaged consisting of low whites compared to cluster 0 and hight african americans, hispanics and asians.

a. Schools in cluster 1, on average, have a higher percentage of African American students? - False

b. Schools in cluster 2, on average, have a higher percentage of African American students? - True, schools in cluster 2 have higher percentage of african americans.

Plot tree with tree.plot_tree¶

  • Use figsize=(25,20)
  • To make the texts of the tree nodes more readable, you add fontsize=16 into tree.plot_tree as another parameter.
In [126]:
plt.figure(figsize=(25,20))
tree.plot_tree(model,fontsize = 16);
In [128]:
plt.figure(figsize=(24,24))
tree.plot_tree(model,
               feature_names = X.columns, 
               class_names=['0','1','2','3'],
               fontsize=20,
               filled = True);

Now, interpret the if-tehn rules. Specifically, extract any two decision (of if-then) rules from the results above.¶

  • If-then rule #1

    • If Pct_Economically_Disadvantaged > 56.55 and Pct_First_Language_Not_English <= 18.15 and Pct_English_Language_Learner <= 12.45 then the student has high needs.

  • If-then rule #2

    • Pct_White > 87.40 and Pct_MultiRace_NonHispanic <= 1.25 class: 0.0 then student belongs to cluster 2 and doesn't really have high needs.

What is the profile of each cluster?¶

  • This results shows "Pct_Native_American","Pct_Students_With_Disabilities", "Pct_Native_Hawaiian_Pacific_Isla",Pct_Males,Pct_Females and "Pct_MultiRace_NonHispanic" are NOT an important factors since about the equal number of students (as indicated by the fact that the mean in each cluster is almost same) and also
  • Profiling
    • cluster 0: high english speakers and low learners with low needs and low in case of economic disadvantage with more whites and low african americans,asians and hispanics.
    • cluster 1: Low english speakers, high learners who have high needs are economically highly disadvantaged consisting of low whites compared to cluster 0 and hight african americans, hispanics and asians.

Compare the results from K-Mean clustering analysis and Agglomerative clustering analysis.¶

  • Since we did 2 level clustering for both the models the mean value results are almost the same in both the cases. In both the cases the most important features are economically disadvantaged,Pct_white,Pct high needs followed by Pct-hispanic and Pct_african. But only difference is cluster centeroids generated bv each algorith while K-Mean algorithm generated cluster 1 with 1271 and cluster 2 has 520 whilst Agglomerative clustering algorithm generated with 1322 in cluster 1 and 437 in cluster 2. But the end result in clustering the data was similar in both cases.
